1
00:01:40,410 --> 00:01:45,930
[Speed and Love]

2
00:01:46,289 --> 00:01:48,830
[Episode 6]

3
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:54,400
Sanlai,

4
00:01:54,670 --> 00:01:56,729
why are we doing this so late at night?

5
00:01:57,430 --> 00:01:58,509
It's all because that guy Brandy

6
00:01:58,509 --> 00:01:59,640
gave me homework,

7
00:02:00,090 --> 00:02:01,720
making me circle left ten times

8
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:02,850
and right ten times.

9
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:05,340
I'm not a donkey.
Why does he keep making me go in circles?

10
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:06,250
Homework?

11
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,400
What else did he give you?

12
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,500
Can I hear about it?

13
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:18,070
Turn toward the center,

14
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:19,620
step on the clutch,

15
00:02:20,070 --> 00:02:21,480
rev the engine hard,

16
00:02:22,030 --> 00:02:24,100
release the clutch quickly
to start the drift,

17
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:25,380
let the tail swing 90 degrees,

18
00:02:25,380 --> 00:02:26,810
ease off, counter-steer,

19
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:28,970
immediately hit the gas
to keep it sliding,

20
00:02:28,970 --> 00:02:31,370
and then adjust the steering and throttle.

21
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:33,680
Did you understand that?

22
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,570
You didn't?

23
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:38,100
Of course I got it right away.

24
00:02:38,690 --> 00:02:39,490
Let's go then.

25
00:02:42,690 --> 00:02:43,690
Clutch out.

26
00:02:49,410 --> 00:02:51,510
No, wait.
Pull the handbrake and then what?

27
00:02:51,510 --> 00:02:52,940
Never mind. It doesn't matter.

28
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:53,970
The first step is always the hardest.

29
00:02:53,970 --> 00:02:55,180
We've got the first circle down.

30
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:55,850
The rest will be easier.

31
00:02:55,850 --> 00:02:56,500
Yes.

32
00:02:56,620 --> 00:02:58,680
Sanlai, you're already doing great.

33
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:01,810
But… this doesn't look much like a circle.

34
00:03:01,810 --> 00:03:02,810
Doesn't matter.

35
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:04,300
As long as I got it to spin.

36
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:06,580
If you want to drift in big circles,

37
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:08,300
you need to
adjust the steering and throttle

38
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:10,090
to increase rear-wheel traction

39
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:11,340
and push the vehicle outward.

40
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:13,200
You need speed to start drifting.

41
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:14,670
Clutch in, floor the gas,

42
00:03:14,690 --> 00:03:16,170
then pop the clutch.

43
00:03:40,690 --> 00:03:41,350
This is fun!

44
00:03:41,740 --> 00:03:43,540
Dad, you're so cool! Do it again!

45
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:44,740
Roller coaster!

46
00:03:44,870 --> 00:03:46,670
See? My daughter takes after me.

47
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:48,970
Hurry up, Dad! One more time!

48
00:03:48,970 --> 00:03:50,690
Alright! Roller coaster!

49
00:03:55,740 --> 00:03:57,020
Faster, Dad!

50
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:00,400
If you want to drift in big circles,

51
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,340
you need to
adjust the steering and throttle

52
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:03,650
to increase rear-wheel traction

53
00:04:03,650 --> 00:04:05,310
and push the vehicle outward.

54
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,640
You seem to have forgotten
to straighten the wheel.

55
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:14,500
Why did you say exactly the same thing
as Brandy did?

56
00:04:16,209 --> 00:04:17,690
Maybe it's just a coincidence.

57
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,180
Sanlai, try again.

58
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:20,970
Remember to straighten the wheel
once you start drifting.

59
00:04:20,970 --> 00:04:22,370
And don't forget the gas.

60
00:04:23,660 --> 00:04:24,390
Okay.

61
00:04:25,330 --> 00:04:26,420
I'm going all out.

62
00:04:42,050 --> 00:04:44,290
Sanlai, you forgot to hit the gas.

63
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:48,330
I want to give it a try.

64
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:50,400
Well, be careful.

65
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,690
I haven't gotten married and had kids yet.

66
00:04:52,690 --> 00:04:54,480
Don't worry. I know what I'm doing.

67
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,940
I'll get the car out first.

68
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:00,790
Well...

69
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:03,810
Just a small mistake.

70
00:05:05,370 --> 00:05:06,970
Have you ever driven before?

71
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:08,620
I haven't,

72
00:05:09,130 --> 00:05:11,380
but I watched my dad drive a lot
when I was a kid.

73
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:13,110
Wait. Let me think for a second.

74
00:05:13,130 --> 00:05:13,930
Wait a minute.

75
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:15,410
Your dad?

76
00:05:15,570 --> 00:05:17,100
Jin Qiang? That alcoholic?

77
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:17,810
Yes.

78
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:18,980
When he was young,

79
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:20,450
he was a great racer.

80
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:23,010
Are we talking about the same person?

81
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,880
Feel the grip in the rear wheels.

82
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:44,250
Feel how the gas and brakes work together.

83
00:05:56,909 --> 00:05:57,590
What...

84
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:00,060
just happened?

85
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:02,420
I told you. Strong genes.

86
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:04,330
Family genes.

87
00:06:05,910 --> 00:06:06,500
Alright.

88
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:07,630
Figure eight.

89
00:06:07,970 --> 00:06:08,580
Let's go.

90
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,950
Brake, brake, brake!

91
00:06:16,370 --> 00:06:17,540
Who drives a car

92
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:19,540
in reverse anyway?

93
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:21,780
Just another small mistake.

94
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,600
Let me try again.

95
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,310
Wait!

96
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:24,950
I'll get out first.

97
00:06:25,330 --> 00:06:26,260
Are you serious?

98
00:06:26,690 --> 00:06:27,620
Sanlai!

99
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:29,690
Be careful.

100
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,630
Ease off the gas, then push.

101
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:42,960
Turn the wheel earlier.

102
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:46,680
Don't wait until the front goes past
before turning the wheel.

103
00:06:58,260 --> 00:06:59,650
You're amazing!

104
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:01,500
Was that impressive?

105
00:07:01,620 --> 00:07:02,370
Yeah.

106
00:07:02,660 --> 00:07:04,120
Let me show you another trick.

107
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:04,880
Be careful!

108
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:15,990
Are you okay?

109
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:24,010
Nana?

110
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,450
Mu!

111
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:28,300
Little fortune teller?

112
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:29,500
You know Jiang Mu too?

113
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:31,100
We met on the plane.

114
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,490
You two know each other?

115
00:07:33,450 --> 00:07:35,010
She was my childhood sweetheart.

116
00:07:35,010 --> 00:07:35,720
Nonsense!

117
00:07:35,740 --> 00:07:37,870
We were just neighbors for a few years.

118
00:07:38,370 --> 00:07:39,050
Mu,

119
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:41,860
I signed you up
for a driving school in Manshi.

120
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:43,320
We can go for lessons soon.

121
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:44,810
That place is great in every way,

122
00:07:44,810 --> 00:07:45,980
except there are no hot guys.

123
00:07:45,980 --> 00:07:46,570
But tonight,

124
00:07:46,570 --> 00:07:48,250
I can take you somewhere with hot guys.

125
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:48,860
Let's go!

126
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:51,100
Get in.

127
00:07:51,710 --> 00:07:54,710
Little fortune teller,
where are you taking Jiang Mu?

128
00:07:58,659 --> 00:07:59,250
Mu,

129
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,620
it's very diverse here.

130
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:02,480
People speak Thai, Chinese, and English.

131
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,940
And there's one special thing—

132
00:08:03,940 --> 00:08:05,060
because of the modified cars,

133
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:07,280
left-hand and right-hand drive vehicles
can race together.

134
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,500
Everyone's used to it.

135
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,230
Nobody finds it strange at all.

136
00:08:11,650 --> 00:08:12,910
Let me show you around!

137
00:08:15,210 --> 00:08:16,330
Welcome to

138
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:19,350
the ultimate vacation destination!

139
00:08:20,150 --> 00:08:21,690
The car modification scene here

140
00:08:21,690 --> 00:08:22,870
is absolutely thriving.

141
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:24,190
As long as a car meets basic standards,

142
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:25,500
it can be legally on the road.

143
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:27,420
I categorize them into three groups:

144
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:29,100
performance,

145
00:08:29,210 --> 00:08:31,620
show, and supercars.

146
00:08:32,370 --> 00:08:33,490
I know supercars.

147
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:34,659
What are the other two?

148
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:35,659
Performance cars

149
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:37,330
aren't about looks.

150
00:08:37,659 --> 00:08:39,780
They may look ordinary,

151
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:42,299
but they have huge modification potential

152
00:08:42,299 --> 00:08:43,020
and handle really well.

153
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:44,179
People who drive these cars

154
00:08:44,179 --> 00:08:45,610
are all thrill-seekers.

155
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:47,060
On the track,

156
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,490
they go all out, risking their lives.

157
00:08:49,690 --> 00:08:51,610
There are often straight-line drag races.

158
00:08:51,610 --> 00:08:53,140
My cousin is into this type.

159
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:57,060
The show cars are over here.

160
00:08:57,420 --> 00:08:59,330
They look extremely gorgeous,

161
00:08:59,450 --> 00:09:01,100
with custom paint and fancy rims,

162
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:03,160
but they're all show and no go—

163
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,850
just good for taking pictures,
not much else.

164
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:06,970
I personally prefer

165
00:09:07,090 --> 00:09:08,400
the supercars.

166
00:09:09,730 --> 00:09:11,060
Look at this sleek line.

167
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:12,970
They've got the looks,

168
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:14,260
they've got the performance,

169
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:16,190
and they're the complete package.

170
00:09:22,620 --> 00:09:23,950
Here comes a muscle car.

171
00:09:26,570 --> 00:09:29,490
Check out this exhaust
and listen to that roar.

172
00:09:29,780 --> 00:09:31,490
It makes you want to step on the gas—

173
00:09:31,490 --> 00:09:32,750
like riding on clouds.

174
00:09:33,450 --> 00:09:35,250
But I'm not really into this car.

175
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:36,900
I think it's a bit too bulky.

176
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:38,360
I still prefer supercars.

177
00:09:51,370 --> 00:09:52,100
Sanlai!

178
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:56,260
Where's Jiang Mu?

179
00:09:56,450 --> 00:09:57,650
You know Nana, right?

180
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:01,330
The little fortune teller
who read fortunes for Wan Qing?

181
00:10:01,330 --> 00:10:01,900
Yes.

182
00:10:02,090 --> 00:10:02,730
Jiang Mu said

183
00:10:02,730 --> 00:10:04,140
they met on the plane.

184
00:10:04,260 --> 00:10:06,590
And tonight,
Nana took her out to have fun.

185
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:16,030
[Jin Zhao]

186
00:10:19,380 --> 00:10:20,180
What's wrong?

187
00:10:20,340 --> 00:10:22,070
She's not answering her phone.

188
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:30,330
A hot guy.

189
00:10:32,490 --> 00:10:34,490
Don't you think he's sexy?

190
00:10:36,690 --> 00:10:38,450
Isn't your guy that type?

191
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:39,660
My guy?

192
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,250
The one called...

193
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:44,690
Jin Zhao.

194
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:47,450
He's not that type.

195
00:10:47,690 --> 00:10:48,890
He's quite arrogant.

196
00:10:50,180 --> 00:10:51,970
Mr. Attitude, huh?

197
00:10:52,130 --> 00:10:54,380
Tell me the details.
I want to hear everything.

198
00:10:54,380 --> 00:10:55,380
Actually...

199
00:10:57,970 --> 00:11:00,610
he usually seems pretty normal.

200
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:01,940
But today

201
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:04,470
he suddenly did something very strange.

202
00:11:04,690 --> 00:11:06,260
He gave me a...

203
00:11:09,660 --> 00:11:10,570
A what?

204
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,500
Why are you being so hesitant?

205
00:11:21,060 --> 00:11:22,650
That wasn't meant for you, right?

206
00:11:22,650 --> 00:11:24,900
I think so. It was probably a mistake.

207
00:11:27,090 --> 00:11:28,540
Could it be…

208
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,480
he has another woman?

209
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,500
I've thought about that too.

210
00:11:35,210 --> 00:11:37,440
I wanted to ask him,

211
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:39,800
but I was afraid it would be awkward.

212
00:11:40,610 --> 00:11:41,490
Sometimes

213
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,370
I wish he would think a little more

214
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:45,300
and not just see me as a sister.

215
00:11:45,650 --> 00:11:47,690
But I'm also afraid he'll overthink it.

216
00:11:47,690 --> 00:11:49,180
If he rejects me,

217
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,760
I won't even get to be his sister anymore.

218
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:54,380
It's so complicated.

219
00:11:55,570 --> 00:11:56,780
You can't just ask him directly.

220
00:11:56,780 --> 00:11:57,610
Right.

221
00:11:57,610 --> 00:12:00,300
But you can test him indirectly.

222
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:01,140
How?

223
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:03,300
Make him think

224
00:12:03,610 --> 00:12:05,020
you have another man.

225
00:12:06,690 --> 00:12:07,570
Isn't that a little inappropriate?

226
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:09,210
What's inappropriate about it?

227
00:12:09,210 --> 00:12:09,970
Listen to me.

228
00:12:10,180 --> 00:12:11,240
This is the only way

229
00:12:11,260 --> 00:12:12,420
you can find out

230
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:14,140
whether he even has

231
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,780
the slightest bit of feeling for you.

232
00:12:19,900 --> 00:12:20,850
It sounds...

233
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:22,330
like a good idea.

234
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:23,090
Exactly.

235
00:12:23,090 --> 00:12:24,890
Where am I supposed to find a guy?

236
00:12:25,330 --> 00:12:26,660
Use what's available.

237
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:28,600
There are so many hot guys here.

238
00:12:29,270 --> 00:12:30,620
[Where have you been?]

239
00:12:31,970 --> 00:12:32,810
Is it him?

240
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:35,310
[Why didn't you pick up?]

241
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:39,460
Don't call him back.

242
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:40,740
Keep him waiting.

243
00:12:41,730 --> 00:12:43,450
There's an old saying in China:

244
00:12:43,450 --> 00:12:45,230
"You can't make a deal
by lowering yourself."

245
00:12:45,230 --> 00:12:47,390
You can't always be the proactive one.

246
00:12:47,690 --> 00:12:49,060
You need to provoke him a little

247
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:49,940
and take back

248
00:12:49,940 --> 00:12:51,610
the initiative.

249
00:12:56,850 --> 00:12:58,570
Don't be afraid of using old tricks.

250
00:12:58,570 --> 00:13:00,210
Old tricks work best.

251
00:13:00,810 --> 00:13:01,490
Really.

252
00:13:01,810 --> 00:13:03,260
Now we just need a guy

253
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:04,730
competitive enough

254
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:06,810
to do us this tiny favor.

255
00:13:08,190 --> 00:13:10,420
Competitive?

256
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,520
Not Liang Yanfeng.

257
00:13:18,830 --> 00:13:19,900
He's a well-known playboy

258
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:21,450
in this circle.

259
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:22,840
Stay away from him.

260
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:25,090
But from what I've seen,

261
00:13:25,090 --> 00:13:27,750
he's the only one
who looks competitive enough.

262
00:13:28,610 --> 00:13:30,470
There's someone better than him.

263
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:36,580
Here he comes.

264
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,120
My cousin, the host tonight,

265
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:42,810
and the birthday boy.

266
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:45,540
-Cousin?
-It's him.

267
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:47,230
Let's go.

268
00:13:47,470 --> 00:13:48,800
I'll take you to see him.

269
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:50,380
Here comes the birthday boy.

270
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:51,310
Happy birthday.

271
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:53,510
You're more excited than I am.

272
00:13:53,510 --> 00:13:55,110
Well, you're my good friend.

273
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:57,670
When have I ever missed your birthday?

274
00:13:57,780 --> 00:13:59,910
Looks to me like you're here for girls.

275
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:02,110
Men are like race cars.

276
00:14:02,330 --> 00:14:05,860
If you're picking one,
pick the one that stands out in every way.

277
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:08,120
Your cousin looks like a foreigner.

278
00:14:08,250 --> 00:14:09,250
Is he mixed-race?

279
00:14:09,420 --> 00:14:11,570
No, pure local.

280
00:14:11,900 --> 00:14:13,020
But you're in luck.

281
00:14:13,050 --> 00:14:14,980
He speaks Chinese fluently.

282
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,010
And...

283
00:14:16,170 --> 00:14:17,780
he likes Chinese girls.

284
00:14:19,310 --> 00:14:20,830
But he looks like a bad guy.

285
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:22,520
No, no, no.

286
00:14:23,180 --> 00:14:24,690
He's never had any

287
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:26,260
questionable women around him.

288
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:27,640
